{"version":2,"depth":"rich","notice":"The contradiction may be the point: loving her well does not require making your loss disappear. Nearly every part of the dream tries to hold two truths in one space—the vase is too narrow, the chairs are repeatedly adjusted, and your face shows congratulations and sadness at once. The careful arranging may be less about preparing for relatives than about trying to make enough room for feelings that refuse to become tidy.

What seems most important is that you never ask your sister to stay, yet she appears to understand what your sentence leaves out. This may be giving shape to a particular wish: to support her freedom without having to hide the cost of it, and to be known without making your sadness her responsibility. Her hand on your shoulder carries the same double meaning as the rest—she remains protective and loving, but cannot protect you from her absence.

The fully set table after nobody arrives adds a quieter possibility: you may be preparing yourself for a changed family arrangement before everyone else has caught up. The ending does not resolve pride into grief or grief into pride. It lets closeness be strong enough to contain both.","threads":["Being understood without asking her to choose","Making room for a bond that is changing, not ending"],"reflection_questions":["In waking life, do you often keep the costly part of your support unspoken and hope your sister will recognize it anyway, or does that feel specific to this dream?"],"confidence":"high","pattern_candidates":[{"type":"relationship","label":"Closeness holding pride and grief together","evidence":"You sincerely congratulate your sister while visibly grieving her departure, and both feelings remain distinct after waking.","confidence":"explicit"},{"type":"action","label":"Leaving the need unspoken","evidence":"You want to ask her to stay but say only that you are happy for her; she appears to hear the missing part.","confidence":"explicit"},{"type":"image","label":"Trying to fit too much into a narrow arrangement","evidence":"The too-narrow vase, repeatedly shifted chairs, and carefully prepared table echo the effort to accommodate conflicting feelings.","confidence":"suggested"},{"type":"relationship","label":"Protection that cannot prevent separation","evidence":"Her hand on your shoulder makes you feel protected and abandoned in the same second.","confidence":"explicit"}]}
